â€¢149; Episode 3: In Episode 3, East Indians Anjan and Harshini Bacchu weather the highs and lows of Silicon Valley's dot.com boom and bust. The second Palestinian Intifada and Sept. 11th profoundly impact Naima in America. The Flores famiy discovers that their long journey from Mexico to Kansas will not be their last. Israel and Ngozi face the most serious tests yet to their dreams in America, while Barine comes within reach of her own American dream. And Dominican baseball players Ricardo and Jose are at career crossroads: Will they make it to the major leagues or not? ; 

